Through the years, I have combined meditation, action, and the Iron into a single strength. I believe that when the body is strong, the mind thinks strong thoughts. Time spent away from the Iron makes my mind degenerate. I wallow in a thick depression. My body shuts down my mind. The Iron is the best antidepressant I have ever found. There is no better way to fight weakness than with strength. Once the mind and body have been awakened to their true potential, it’s impossible to turn back.

The Iron never lies to you. You can walk outside and listen to all kinds of talk, get told that you’re a god or a total bastard. The Iron will always kick you the real deal. The Iron is the great reference point, the all-knowing perspective giver. Always there like a beacon in the pitch black. I have found the Iron to be my greatest friend. It never freaks out on me, never runs. Friends may come and go. But two hundred pounds is always two hundred pounds.

Gained 27 pounds in 4 weeks.  Feel great and lovin life.

It’s been a crazy six months for me with big decisions and having to act more like a man the older I get. The choices that I have made were some of the best I have made in my life and much more important that what I had first thought. I'm very happy now and it’s not just a day to day. There is a tomorrow and for the first time I'm starting to plan for it a little bit more. I first thought that my decisions were all on me and that I was the reason for it all. A little time and clarity have shown me that I was wrong. It was never all on me I just tried to put it all on me to hold the burden. Not anymore I have been shown that it wasn't all me and that my role was me evolving and changing. I am in love again and it scares me to death but at the same time I really haven't felt this alive. I look forward to my life with my friends and family. This February has been incredible. I took off a week to celebrate my birthday, to take vacation with my starfish, and to just relax for a bit. Valentines was one of the best days I have ever had and the love and feelings followed threw all week. Small note *honey dust is an incredible thing you should all try it once. I turned 34 and as always was humbled by the vast array of friends who helped me celebrate. On the 17th we had a small intimate dinner. It turned out to be one of the best times and meals I had ever experienced there. Surrounded by good friends that I sometimes lose the sight of. I thank you; you made me look again at myself and what I have. I am truly thankful. Then on the 20th we all went out to Packard's for drinks to celebrate. Small thing like meeting up are truly huge and underrated. Again I am humbled by the people who came out and from the friends who couldn't make it but sent well wishes and love. The character of a man can be defined by thus who he calls friends and surrounds him with. Because of you I am a better person and bigger man. Thanks I owe you all. I may not show it or let you see it but I know this debt is one I will be paying back my whole life.
Been along time since I puked in the snow.  Fuck it.

It's been a long time since I have had this taste.  I had almost forgotten what it was.  I don't remember it being so sweet thou.  It scares the hell outta me.  It's been a long time my friend.  I hope it stays with me awhile. It tickles my throat and warms my cheeks.  It has been to long in coming but worth all the wait.

<![endif]-->  <p class="MsoNormal">Ah a truly different start to a new year.  Normally I would start the year the way I ended it drunk, out of control, and not caring about the 2nd.  Stealing as much attention as I could and feeding on the energy, good or bad like a narcissistic asshole.  Different this year soft, calm and in control.  I remember last year only 2 small black spots but in the end so much more than any year from the last 5.  Hard thing to do, to not want to grab that energy.  Hard to sit still when the inner child in you rages because it no longer gets its way.  I miss something’s and some people. Time is a funny thing it still moves and it’s time to flow with it and not try to stop it.  I’ve dropped 18 pounds and lost 6% of my body fat.  I have found the control I have with my body can be used to control myself right now.  New goals are now to gain 15 pounds this winter/spring.  I started today with a trainer and a new style and method at the gym.  I need to now slow it down and not work out so much or so hard.  Funny I thought that harder meant better but atlas to fall is to pick yourself back up.  So here is to a new year my friends.  I love you all.  You’re in my thoughts and in my heart</p>

Waking up a little more bit by bit.I took a trip to Boston last weekend.  I have been saying I was going to go for years but never really wanted to or had any inclination to.  Starting to come alive in places that have been absent for a long time.  Blue man group was so much more then I expected.  I could have used Niki's help in the north end thou for the Italian food. I did all right thou.  Here are a few Pictures of the view from the hotel 20th floor.  The last pic is one I did panoramic so a full view is a must, one of the best pictures I have ever made.  just thought i would share and let people know I'm OK.

It's been a long time since I could let parts of myself out that I hid.  Reminds me of those moments when you see things that you see all the time but now you actually see them.  Like when going to work at night and looking up seeing all the stars.  Driving down a road and noticing the colors of the grass and the contrasts of the tree's to their surroundings.  I think I have finally been able to let Elizabeth go.  I hide and guarded things from even my most trusting friends.  Not because I think they will betray my trust but due to having to face things that don't always look in my eyes as how I should look or feel.  I forgot the part of me that loved her and held onto the part that hated her.  Have you ever noticed that it’s usually the ones you loved first that you can hate?  I took pictures off the wall that I said I would never take off.  Ones I would look at, sneak peeks at, and say what if.  Where would I be?  I feel naked at times now.  Now I can’t go to where I feel familiar and comfortable.  I need to listen again.  It feels good to be held and not feel numb, to first want to give before receiving.   The air tastes a little sweeter and the dust doesn’t dry out my lungs anymore.  To not feed my ego and to be against my own grain.  To be out and sit and let someone else take the limelight kills me.  To sit and be calm when all that I have ever done was take that light and run. I’ve ramble off again.  To really love her I know that she needed what I wasn’t, what I didn’t have.  She found him and is happy.  I am able to say now good, I’m glad you have found what you were looking for.  Irony in life is hearing maybe you haven’t suffered enough to get to that next level.  I think I have paid my dues.  Let’s see now where we go.  I gladly give another eight years of sorrow for one day of true happiness.  Release and let go, release....

Just one of thous days where the small things stick out and you notice them more.  Stepped outside tonight and notice that the skyline was so clear and clean.  Clusters and clusters of stars.  All varying in color and brightness.  It's also cold right down to the core cold.  Mixed together they make a beautiful night.  The leaves are all gone now and the naked stalks of the branches are all sticking up like withered bones.  With the right skyline of blue and gray its doesn't come across as gloomy but more of just a world just fallen asleep.  Candlelight is flickering just right playing games and dancing on the wall.  Just burning with no intent other then to burn out.  It's been a good day, just being in today. hmm time to lay down and dance in my dreams once again.

Broken away and shattered, like glass that fell from a desolated table top area and landed on a hard linoeum floor, I lay astray and paralysed. It's as if I have fallen from the sky and ended upon top of a broken flat frame of a world full of misguidence, pain, and misfortune. In a hell that hasn't been discovered and that would soon be shaded full of darkness from which was nothing, but demons and the uncivilized either chained to a brick wall, or sunken into a black hole.
Why of all people do I be broken away from the blue and green surface, and everything that is unbroken?
Was it something that I have done?
Was it something that I haven't yet overcome?

Maybe I was broken away from all that is unbroken and spiritual, because it was meant to be as a lack of self-confidence or a great sign of sensitivity. Or even it could be because of an activity that I haven't yet witnessed and was not a part of. Purpose that even if I wasn't a part of which that was eliminated of the blue and green surface and everything that is unbroken, wouldn't it still mean that I have yet been broken away?

Author: 	Kevin Jacobs

I forgot why I took that first step. The start to the end or rather just a step with out reflection.  What I thought was straight is really now a circle.  Taken from view and laid down upon with heavy head.  I sit now to clear my head, to subside my anger. To stay and clear is finally a lesson to understand. When the past dictates the future, the future then becomes a variant of the past.  Breath, just breath the rest comes in time.

Sad but not enough to cry, happy but not enough to sing.  Full of rage, full of anger.  To rip flesh from bone.   
Scream at the sky with a voice that has no sound.  Tired, weary, filled with angst.  Seeing but not knowing. Tender but not in sight.  Bottled, locked in, broken out. Shy but outgoing.  Snipe, snap, bark, gripe.  Other side of the pillow.  Warmth of sun, chill of rain.  Talkative nothing to say.  Weight, burden, lines drawn.  No forgiveness, unforgiving, unyielding, stubborn.  Cold, muddled, grey.

A story not told.  Pieces of a puzzle, missing holes.  More truth then admitted.  Rest, shower then bed. Long weeks, longer winter.  The tariffs price grows higher.

Lego goes MMO
NetDevil, toy company team up to build massively multiplayer online "gaming experience"; details yet to be announced.


Lego my MMO!

One of the simplest toys of all time has found a profitable home in one of the most technologically advanced areas of entertainment. Lego building blocks have parlayed their appeal into video games, with the brand taking the spotlight in a pair of Star Wars-branded games from developer Traveller's Tales, as well as several other games over the past decade.

Now, the interlocking toys will venture into another hot avenue of gaming--the massively multiplayer online space. Lego Group today announced that it is partnering with Colorado-based NetDevil to create a "massively multiplayer online gaming experience."

Lego has not yet announced any specifics on the game, leaving the window open for speculation on what the game will entail. NetDevil previously created the vehicular MMOG Auto Assault. However, the emphasis on attracting a younger audience means the Lego MMOG is likely to go the way of Ubisoft's Puzzle Pirates, which has a very Lego-influenced visual style.

The Devil is often a great card for business success; hard work and ambition.


Perhaps the most misunderstood of all the major arcana, the Devil is not really "Satan" at all, but Pan the half-goat nature god and/or Dionysius. These are gods of pleasure and abandon, of wild behavior and unbridled desires. This is a card about ambitions; it is also synonymous with temptation and addiction. On the flip side, however, the card can be a warning to someone who is too restrained, someone who never allows themselves to get passionate or messy or wild - or ambitious. This, too, is a form of enslavement. As a person, the Devil can stand for a man of money or erotic power, aggressive, controlling, or just persuasive. This is not to say a bad man, but certainly a powerful man who is hard to resist. The important thing is to remember that any chain is freely worn. In most cases, you are enslaved only because you allow it.
